{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"dd810fdf-6898-48e2-8b39-489866348ba2","content":"Build succeeds. Here's the summary:\n\n**Why it breaks in MSTest v3:** The non-generic `Assert.AreEqual(object, object)` was removed. The new signature is `Assert.AreEqual<T>(T, T)`. When the compiler can't infer a single `T` from mismatched argument types (e.g., `string` vs `object`), you get CS1503.\n\n**How to fix:**\n- **Best:** Add `<object>` — e.g., `Assert.AreEqual<object>(expected, actual)`\n- **Alternative:** Cast both args to the same type — e.g., `Assert.AreEqual((object)str, actual)`\n\n`Assert.AreSame` was left unchanged since it already requires reference-type args of the same type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f02ae7c0-bf05-4551-97f1-06988b375832","outputTokens":186},"id":"e1825461-eac0-4227-ae59-a3645041c782","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:56:15.591Z","parentId":"82a1149d-6a0a-4257-aef5-57d49da51a42"}
